a. update the conduct of the physical inventory of all properties of the LGU annually and submit annual physical inventory report of Property Plant and Equipment;
b. ensure that all properties of the municipality issued to officer and employees shall be covered by Property Acknowledgement Receipt (PAR), which shall be renewed every January of the third year after issue; 
c. require the Accounting Department to maintain a separate updated subsidiary ledgers of property plant and equipment to support the general ledger accounts to ensure completeness of the recorded amounts in the books of accounts; and
d. require the General Services Officer to prepare and maintain property cards and reconcile regularly with the accounting records.

